title: PML-N’s Muhammad Khan wins PB-5 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) Muhammad Khan has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-5, Loralai by securing 14,424 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ulma-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI) Molvi Faiz Ullah who bagged 12,456 votes.
Overall voters’ turnout remained 46.47 percent.
